  "name": "Morrison COU1 \u2014 CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). An extensive uncertainty quantification campaign was conducted covering inlet flow rate, rotational speed, and fluid viscosity; the UQ results informed the validation comparison and confirmed that model predictions remain within acceptable bounds across the parameter space. Sensitivity rankings from the UQ campaign are discussed in the validation report referenced under hasValidationResult.",
