      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Experimental comparison of CFD-predicted hemolysis index against in-vitro measurements for 5 operating points",
      "description": "CFD predictions of normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro measurements at five flow-speed combinations. All predictions within \u00b115% of experimental values; RH < 1 for all operating points. The UQ campaign (Latin hypercube sampling, n=200 runs) explored sensitivity to inlet velocity, rotational speed, and blood viscosity; Sobol indices confirmed rotational speed as the dominant driver of hemolysis variance (S1=0.61). These UQ findings are reported in the accompanying technical report but are not separately linked as a structured sensitivity analysis node in this package version."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/mesh-convergence-study",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence and discretization error quantification for centrifugal pump CFD model",
      "description": "Grid convergence index (GCI) study performed across three mesh refinement levels (4.2M, 11.7M, 28.4M cells). GCI for NIH at worst-case operating point: 3.8%. Richardson extrapolation confirms asymptotic convergence. Discretization error bounded and acceptable for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/code-verification-mms",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Numerical code verification via method of manufactured solutions for Navier-Stokes solver",
      "description": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to the incompressible Navier-Stokes solver. Second-order spatial convergence confirmed. No code defects identified affecting hemolysis scalar transport."
    }
  ],
